\begin_layout Subsection
Demanding task for operators
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Being able to act within seconds during operations of LHC is one of the
 challenges of operator.
 It's a demanding responsibility that may be stressful for some people.
 DAQ system is a complex system therefore there are tools to automate certain
 operations, e.g.
 staring the run, stopping, reseting, resyncing etc.
 This facilitates the actions initiated by operators, however, it's not
 uncommon that the system goes into erroneous state where deeper understanding
 of the system is required to overcome the problem in the optimal way.
 Experts of a given subsystems prepare instructions for operators for specific
 problems.
 These are recovery instructions needed to resume the data-taking as soon
 as possible.
 There is no need for operators to learn insights of all subsystems nor
 to understand the problem.
 They need to overcome it and make sure the operations of CMS go smoothly.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Over a time the list of recovery instruction grew.
 Even though it's prepared by experts in easy form of checklist helping
 to identify the problem it takes considerable amount of time to find the
 correct one.
 The reaction time of the operator increased as it was difficult to remember
 all of them.
 Wrong or suboptimal decision were not uncommon as well.
 This lead to increased recovery time.
 Figure 
