\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
They differ significantly in terms of impact they have on system and how
 much time they take to complete.
 One of the habits we've observed is issuing the most versatile recovery
 action when unnecessary.
 The operator on one hand can issue general-purpose, heavy recovery action
 and be sure that it will fix the problem.
 On the other hand they can try to find out some light highly-specific to
 given circumstances action.
 It might be less stressful to follow the first way.
 In the latter case the problem needs to be correctly identified to be successfu
l.
